data.value: With his boy-ish looks and a similar action, a teen-aged Adam Zampa drew immediate comparisons with Shane Warne. With the old-school technique of tossing the ball above the eye-line and wily deception, Adam Zampa burst onto the scene when he represented Australia U-19 in their successful 2010 World Cup campaign, when scouts and experts recognized the rather familiar action.
